Chapter 3 cross validation from abhishek thakur's book.
https://neptune.ai/blog/cross-validation-in-machine-learning-how-to-do-it-right
larger k will take lot of time to train so if dataset is large use small k,
in deep learning use hold out based or train, valid, test approach coz it takes lots of time to train.
always use stratified k fold for classification so that it will handle class imbalance
